data.enText: to organize the different parts of an activity and the people involved in it so that it works well

data.chText: 为协调这个队的工作，他们任用了一位新经理。
data.enText: They appointed a new manager to coordinate the work of the team.

data.chText: 我们需要拿出解决这一问题的协调一致的办法。
data.enText: We need to develop a coordinated approach to the problem.

data.chText: 使（身体各部分）动作协调；协同动作
data.enText: to make the different parts of your body work well together
if you coordinate clothes, furniture, etc. or if they coordinate , they look nice together

data.chText: 这种深浅的颜色可与很多颜色搭配。
data.enText: This shade coordinates with a wide range of other colours.

data.chText: 这场运动需要一个强有力的协调人。
data.enText: The campaign needs an effective coordinator.
either of two numbers or letters used to fix the position of a point on a map or graph

data.chText: 一条线上任意一点的x、y 坐标
data.enText: the x, y coordinates of any point on a line
pieces of clothing that can be worn together because, for example, the colours look good together

simple_means.memory_skill: co 共同 + ordin 命令；秩序 + ate 表动词 →〔使〕秩序一样 → 协作

means: 使(身体各部分)动作协调

tr: a number that identifies a position relative to an axis

example: Can you help me organize my files?

tr: bring (components or parts) into proper or desirable coordination correlation
example: align the wheels of my car

tr: bring into common action, movement, or condition
example: coordinate the painters, masons, and plumbers
coordinate his actions with that of his colleagues

tr: of equal importance, rank, or degree

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /kəʊ'ɔːdɪneɪt/. The noun is pronounced /kəʊ'ɔːdɪnət/. 动词读作 /kəʊ'ɔːdɪneɪt/，名词读作 /kəʊ'ɔːdɪnət/。

value.def: If you co-ordinate an activity, you organize the various people and things involved in it.

example.ex: Government officials visited the earthquake zone on Thursday morning to co-ordinate the relief effort.
example.tran: 星期四上午，政府官员视察地震灾区，以协调救援工作。

example.ex: ...the setting up of an advisory committee to co-ordinate police work.
example.tran: 建立咨询委员会以协调警务工作

example.ex: ...a rapid and well co-ordinated international rescue operation.
example.tran: 迅速而且协调有序的国际救援行动

example.ex: ...the party's campaign co-ordinator, Mr Peter Mandelson.
example.tran: 该党的竞选协调人，彼得·曼德尔森先生

value.def: If you co-ordinate clothes or furnishings that are used together, or if they co-ordinate, they are similar in some way and look nice together.

example.ex: She'll show you how to co-ordinate pattern and colours...
example.tran: 她会教你如何搭配款式和颜色。

example.ex: Tie it with fabric bows that co-ordinate with other furnishings...
example.tran: 系上与其他装饰相配的布质蝴蝶结。

example.ex: Colours and looks must fit the themes of the seasons so that the shops co-ordinate well.
example.tran: 颜色和外观必须符合季节的主题，这样各个商家看起来才会比较协调。
窗帘和与之搭配的床罩

value.def: Co-ordinates are pieces of clothing or soft furnishings which are similar and which are intended to be worn or used together.
If you co-ordinate the different parts of your body, you make them work together efficiently to perform particular movements.

example.ex: They spend several weeks each year undergoing intensive treatment which enables them to coordinate their limbs better.
example.tran: 他们每年都花费几周的时间接受强化治疗，以使四肢能够更好地协调。

value.def: The co-ordinates of a point on a map or graph are the two sets of numbers or letters that you need in order to find that point.

example.ex: Can you give me your co-ordinates?
example.tran: 您能告诉我您的坐标吗？

example.ex: ...the latitude and longitude co-ordinates of any location in the world.
